doc:
Swaps elements at indices `i` and `j`.

`i` and `j` may be equal.

Element at index 0 is the front of the queue.

# Panics

Panics if either index is out of bounds.

# Examples

```
use std::collections::VecDeque;

let mut buf = VecDeque::new();
buf.push_back(3);
buf.push_back(4);
buf.push_back(5);
assert_eq!(buf, [3, 4, 5]);
buf.swap(0, 2);
assert_eq!(buf, [5, 4, 3]);
```
